“

The epidemic is not over, but life goes on.

”

“

The epidemic is not over, but life goes on.

”

At present, the prevention and control of the epidemic situation of new coronavirus in China has entered a critical moment. According to the assessment of a report released by the Shanghai Institute of International Studies on the 14th, the development trend of the national epidemic situation has continued to stabilize and improve, and the emergence time of the turning point of the overall epidemic situation, will depend on China's current epidemic prevention measures and the level of cooperation of the entire population.

Over the weekend, people from Beijing and Shanghai were still rare. Residents wear face masks, go out to purchase essential daily necessities and receive express delivery. In Haidian District's Huayuan Road Subdistrict, Beijing Community, where this reporter lives, streets are closed, and people and vehicles are required to show temporary passes and vehicle passes. The gates of each housing estate are sealed, leaving only one entrance. Basic Food and some daily necessities can be purchased in supermarkets on the streets of the community.
